cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a unified multi-task learning framework for weakly supervised semantic segmentation and saliency detection using a single network. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks, specifically image segmentation and saliency detection, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques and end-to-end training, which are common in the sub-categories cs.LG and cs.AI. Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on benchmark datasets, which is a characteristic of papers in the sub-categories cs.MM and cs.NE.
